5:
Building a town in the sky... I see... How 
very impertinent for dirt-crawlers.
10: Hello, Vagner. Are you out for a walk?
14:
Mind thy manners, little one. I am to be 
addressed with my titles. Vagner the 
Mighty, Vagner the All-Consuming, 
Vagner the Terrible!
18:
I am not "little one." My name is Stella.
This is now the fifth time I have told 
you.
21:
Thy name merits no spot in these 
ancient memories.
24:
Do you have trouble remembering 
names? ...You ARE quite old.
27:
Fortune favors the bold, they say, but 
I say death awaits the brazen.
Dost thou wish for a fiery demise?
34: Art thou not afeared of me?
41:
I am the inferno! My flames consume 
the flesh and purge the soul. Many 
a warrior a traipsed to my den and 
paid dearly for their insolence.
43:
I act as tyrant, judge, and executioner!
Yet thou gazest at me with unclouded 
eyes. Do I not cast even the slightest 
pall over thy heart?
46:
I don't really feel anything... but 
perhaps.
54:
I have very little data on dragons, 
including you.
56: I require more to form an opinion.
61:
I have heard enough. Thou art a fool. 
Even fear is no cure for stupidity. 
Get out of my sight.
64: Not before I have collected more data.
69: There is no need for this "data"!
73: I would argue that there is.
83:
Hey, Alk. Look over there. I think 
a storm's brewing.
87: Ooh... Battle of the heavyweights, huh?
91:
Place your bets. My money's on the 
500 ton dragon.
94:
Please... Has Stella ever backed down 
from ANYTHING?
98: You know, Light has spoken about you.
104:
Yes. He said that you were a great and 
powerful dragon.
105:
Then he told the story of how he 
battled you for seven days and seven 
nights, but neither could claim victory. 
No one believed him though.
110:
"Neither" could claim victory? 
NEITHER?!
HE would not deliver the final blow! But 
in sparing my life, he subjected me to 
a humiliation worse than death!
114:
Has he forgotten this?!
Then I shall sear it into his skull again!
120: Vagner, you are an admirer of Light's.
127:
Isn't that why you chased him to 
Starview?
129:
There is a term for people like you…
Ah. Fanboy.
136:
I seek only a conclusion to our battle! 
An end to this farce!
140:
Then you should be working to return 
Light to his original form.
143:
It is the most logical way to get what 
you want.
147:
Hah. Dost thou hope to treat with me? 
To talk me into aiding a champion?
149:
Thy quest shall fail. There is naught left 
of the man I once fought but a frail 
and empty husk.
152: He is not a husk. He is our champion.
155:
Mm... I must say, thine eyes intrigue 
me... Untouched as of yet by fear or 
doubt.
157: Very well, little one. I shall play along...
159:
...If only to watch cold despair run 
through thy veins for the first time…
170:
Perhaps there's an issue with his 
memory processing...
